INTREPRETER:

1.  Translates program one statement at  a time .
2.  Intrepretes line by line .
3.  Takes less time to analyse the code.
4.  Debugging is easy.
5.  Programming languages like Python, Ruby are used.

COMPILER:

1.  Scans the entire program and translates the whole into machine code .
2.  Generates error message after analysing the whole code.
3.  Takes more time to analyse the code.
4.  Debugging is hard.
5.  Programming languages like C, C++ are used.


